), male S2 with sub-reniform and transverse black spots (Fig. 7B) (sub-triangular and longitudinal in 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. ignifascia" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" rank="species" species="ignifascia">C. ignifascia</taxonomicName>
, Fig. 7A), and T3 with darkened clover-shaped spot (Figs 6E, 6F).
</paragraph>
